{"type":"message","id":"ba26e4c2","parentId":"2660819c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T20:51:29.625Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_efe4urb30xrf_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5185\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2396\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\n[mutation proposed] a\n[master 2921d24] pulse: 2026-03-23 165102\n 7 files changed, 338 insertions(+), 141 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 165102.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 165102.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 164101.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 165102 - The TIC Experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1 advancement, but there's no implementation yet. The hypothesis is clear: causal structure IS invariant structure, and we need to test this on the pulse logs.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"sharp-harbor","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5185\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2396\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\n[mutation proposed] a\n[master 2921d24] pulse: 2026-03-23 165102\n 7 files changed, 338 insertions(+), 141 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 165102.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 165102.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 164101.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 165102 - The TIC Experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1 advancement, but there's no implementation yet. The hypothesis is clear: causal structure IS invariant structure, and we need to test this on the pulse logs.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774299089621}}
{"type":"message","id":"efb23b67","parentId":"ba26e4c2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T20:51:29.630Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_efe4urb30xrf_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 164101\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine ONE concrete action that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- Key insight: Compression-Causal Duality - causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Next action defined: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n- Need to: Implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step from the pending actions is to implement the TIC experiment. I should:\r\n1. Look at the pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier or at minimum, set up the experiment framework\r\n\r\nSince I'm Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent, I need to be specific about a file edit.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most actionable item is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nA concrete action would be to create a script or document that sets up this experiment. Let me look at what files exist and what makes sense.\r\n\r\nGiven the insight that \"causal structure IS invariant structure\", I should create:\r\n1. A TIC implementation approach/plan, or\r\n2. Actually start implementing the classifier\r\n\r\nThe most concrete file edit would be to create the TIC experiment implementation. Let me create a Python script or document that begins this implementation.\r\n\r\nActually, since the goals mention:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nI should create a script that does this. Let me create a simple TIC classifier implementation.\r\n\r\nBut wait - I should check if logs directory exists. Let me think about what's most actionable.\r\n\r\nGiven the compression-causal duality insight, a good concrete action would be to:\r\n1. Create a TIC implementation script that reads pulse logs and classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n2. Or create the experiment specification document\r\n\r\nLet me go with creating a Python implementation of the TIC classifier. This advances the Phase 1 goal directly.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY insight provides a concrete path forward: implement Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) to test if causal structure = invariant structure. Need to build the classifier on existing pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate TIC classifier implementation that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and tests the compression-causation hypothesis empirically.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d+)\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_blocks(log_file):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key-value content blocks from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    blocks = {}\r\n    with open(log_file, 'r') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    # Extract goals, observations, actions\r\n    sections = re.split(r'###\\s+', content)\r\n    for section in sections:\r\n        if section.startswith('GOALS'):\r\n            blocks['goals'] = section\r\n        elif section.startswith('RECENT'):\r\n            blocks['recent'] = section\r\n    return blocks\r\n\r\ndef detect_invariants(pulse_logs):\r\n    \"\"\"Identify content that persists across pulses = causal structure.\"\"\"\r\n    invariant_tags = [\r\n        'Phase', 'COMPLETE', 'PENDING', 'Architecture', 'Compression',\r\n        'Insight', 'Goal', 'Action', 'MUTATION', 'file:'\r\n    ]\r\n    variant_tags = ['Observation', 'timestamp', 'date', 'This Session']\r\n    \r\n    invariant_count = 0\r\n    variant_count = 0\r\n    all_content = []\r\n    \r\n    for log in sorted(pulse_logs):\r\n        with open(log, 'r') as f:\r\n            content = f.read()\r\n        for tag in invariant_tags:\r\n            invariant_count += content.count(tag)\r\n        for tag in variant_tags:\r\n            variant_count += content.count(tag)\r\n        all_content.append(content)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'invariant_hits': invariant_count,\r\n        'variant_hits': variant_count,\r\n        'ratio': invariant_count / (invariant_count + variant_count + 1),\r\n        'pulse_count': len(pulse_logs)\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants, current_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Use invariants to predict next pulse structure.\"\"\"\r\n    # Predict: goals persist, observations change, actions execute\r\n    predictions = {\r\n        'persistent': ['Goals', 'Phase', 'Pending Actions'],\r\n        'will_change': ['Observation', 'timestamp', 'Recent'],\r\n        'will_execute': ['Next Action', 'MUTATION']\r\n    }\r\n    return predictions\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_logs = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_logs) < 2:\r\n        print(\"Need at least 2 pulse logs for TIC experiment\")\r\n        return None\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"Analyzing {len(pulse_logs)} pulse logs...\")\r\n    \r\n    # Detect invariants\r\n    stats = detect_invariants(pulse_logs)\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"\\n=== TIC Results ===\")\r\n    print(f\"Invariant hits: {stats['invariant_hits']}\")\r\n    print(f\"Variant hits: {stats['variant_hits']}\")\r\n    print(f\"Invariant ratio: {stats['ratio']:.2%}\")\r\n    print(f\"\\nClassification accuracy target: >70%\")\r\n    print(f\"Prediction accuracy target: >60%\")\r\n    \r\n    # Success criteria\r\n    if stats['ratio'] > 0.70:\r\n        print(\"\\n✓ Invariant/variant classification: PASS (>70%)\")\r\n    else:\r\n        print(f\"\\n✗ Invariant\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 16:41:24\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774299089625}}
